      <bioghist>
         <head>Biographical/Historical Information</head>
         <p>William Lewis Day was born 20 July 1830, in Spotsylvania
         County, Virginia. He was elected lieutenant of Company D, 30th
         Virginia Infantry, rising to the rank of captain. Day resigned
         from his command 3 February 1863, and later joined Company E,
         9th Virginia Cavalry. After the war, Day became a successful
         farmer in Spotsylvania County. He married Fannie W. Andrews
         (b. 1861) 12 March 1890. Day died 8 June 1897.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>Receipts from John Tyler (ca. 1788-1868), dated 28 February
         1857, and from Ira E. Lipscomb (ca. 1795-1864), dated 3
         January 1858, to William L. Day (1830-1897) for Day's
         purchases of slaves.</p>
      </scopecontent>
